Meet <b>Stephanie</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Stephanie lives at <a href='/home/?user=suavesperk'>25003 Broadway Boulevard</a>, in the busy neighborhood of Metro Park. She has been a citizen of Millsberry since January 1st of 2005, and has made plenty of great friends during her short time at Millsberry Academy.<br><br>Stephanie's popularity at Millsberry Academy is due mostly to her great personality. She is a very friendly girl, who is kind and generous to everyone she meets. She is also quite witty, and always has a great comeback to make her friends laugh.<br><br>At school, Stephanie enjoys her English class most. She really likes writing and has become quite good at it. Why, just last week, she got the highest score on a writing test given in Mrs. Seashore's class.<br><br>After school, Stephanie gets together with her teammates from the Millsberry Academy girls' softball team for practice. Since it's currently winter, they mostly stay in shape by stretching, jogging, and doing aerobics in the Millsberry gym. By the time next season starts, she's hoping to earn a spot in the team's pitching rotation.<br><br>After she comes home from school, Stephanie enjoys practicing her artistic abilities by drawing all sorts of things. Recently, she's been drawing pictures of her new pet&mdash;a beautiful dog she got from the Pet Palace!<br><br>On weekends, Stephanie often spends time at her best friend's house, listening to music such as rap, rhythm & blues, and pop.<br><br>When they have some extra Millsbucks to spend, Stephanie and her friends will usually head to the Clothing Store, in search of a stunning new outfit. Stephanie always has her eyes open for pink, light blue, and red clothes, as those are her favorite colors. During the evening, she and her friends usually head down to the Downtown Entertainment Complex and catch a late movie.<br><br>Congratulations on being such a wonderful citizen, Stephanie!</div>
